    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>hake fillet[s] </strong>with<strong> </strong>your <strong>ground sumac</strong>, <strong>remaining garlic </strong>and a grind of <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until cooked through – this is your <strong>garlicky hake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
